blackball
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:black and white striped boiled sweet; a hard, round, black sweet with white stripes, similar to a

`brandyball': in general English often called humbug. ;
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1910 W.H.B. Orsman; ca1920s J. Winchester ;ca1930s-50s Havelock; [1930s-40s] I could've screamed sitting around the copshop like a half-sucked blackball
